title: PPPP’s Jam Abdul Karim Bijar wins NA-229 election
content:
ISLAMABAD, Feb 9 (APP): Pakistan People’s Party Parliamentarian (PPPP) Candidate Jam Abdul Karim Bijar has won the election for National Assembly constituency NA-229 Malir-I by securing 55,732 votes.
According to the unofficial result issued by the Returning Officer/ECP, his runner-up was Pakistan Muslim League Nawaz candidate Qadir Bakhsh, who bagged 21,841 votes.
Overall voters’ turn-out remained 45.62 percent.
